---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const effectiveDate = 'April 21, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Arsovo"
  description="How Arsovo collects, uses, and protects your information."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12 sm:py-16">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-900 mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mb-10">Effective date: {effectiveDate}</p>

    <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none text-slate-800">
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains what information Arsovo ("we", "our", or "us") collects when you
        visit <strong>arsovo.com</strong> (the "Site"), how we use it, and what choices you have. We try to
        keep this short and readable.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information we collect</h2>
      <p>
        We collect the minimum information needed to operate the Site and serve advertising. This includes:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Log data</strong> automatically collected by our hosting provider (Cloudflare): IP address, user agent, timestamp, referrer, pages requested.</li>
        <li><strong>Analytics data</strong> (if enabled): aggregated, de-identified traffic data from Google Analytics or a similar tool.</li>
        <li><strong>Advertising data</strong> via Google AdSense, which may include cookies and device identifiers used to show relevant ads. See Section 4.</li>
        <li><strong>Information you send us</strong> if you email us (your email address and message content).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. How we use information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To operate, maintain, and improve the Site.</li>
        <li>To understand aggregate traffic patterns.</li>
        <li>To serve and measure advertising.</li>
        <li>To respond to your messages.</li>
        <li>To detect and prevent abuse.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        Cookies are small files stored on your device. We use first-party cookies only for essential site
        functionality. Third-party cookies may be set by Google AdSense and analytics services — see below.
      </p>
      <p>
        You can disable cookies in your browser settings. Doing so will not break the Site, but some
        features may not work as expected.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Google AdSense &amp; third-party advertising</h2>
      <p>
        We use Google AdSense to display ads. Google and its advertising partners, including third-party
        vendors, may use cookies and similar technologies to serve ads based on your prior visits to this
        and other websites.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads based on your visits to this and other sites.</li>
        <li>You can opt out of personalized advertising by visiting <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Google Ads Settings</a>.</li>
        <li>You can also opt out of third-party vendor use of cookies for personalized advertising by visiting <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">aboutads.info</a>.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>5. GDPR (European Economic Area visitors)</h2>
      <p>
        If you are in the EEA, UK, or Switzerland, you have the right to access, correct, delete, or
        restrict processing of your personal data, and the right to data portability. Contact
        <a href="mailto:privacy@arsovo.com">privacy@arsovo.com</a> to exercise these rights.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our legal basis for processing data is legitimate interest in operating and improving the Site,
        and — where required — your consent (for advertising cookies).
      </p>

      <h2>6. CCPA (California residents)</h2>
      <p>
        California residents have the right to know what personal information we collect, request deletion
        of personal information, and opt out of the "sale" of personal information. We do not sell
        personal information in the ordinary sense of the word. Contact
        <a href="mailto:privacy@arsovo.com">privacy@arsovo.com</a> for requests.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Data retention</h2>
      <p>
        Server logs are retained for up to 90 days. Analytics data is retained per the provider's default
        retention period. Email correspondence is retained for as long as needed to respond and for legal
        recordkeeping.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Children</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal
        information from children under 13.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. Material changes will be announced on this page with a
        new effective date.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy? Email <a href="mailto:privacy@arsovo.com">privacy@arsovo.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
